<blockquote>   <p>"Lets say we have n x n matrix and we want to fill this matrix with numbers 1   to n^2.</p>      <p>Sum of distances from element to next element should be max.</p>      <p>Distance between 2 elements is defined as sum of i and j, coordinates of element in matrix. Example for 2 x 2. </p>      <p>13<br>     42</p>      <p>Distance 1 to 2 = 2 (1+1).          2 to 3 = 1.          3 to 4 = 2.</p>      <p>Distance d(n=2) = 5.</p>      <p>Find d(n), n-Integer."</p> </blockquote>